INSERT INTO `tb_article` VALUES (4, 1, '[]HTTP', NULL, '<div id=\"header\"><h2>HTTP</h2></div><div id=\"post_detail\"><div class=\"post\"><div class=\"postText\"><div id=\"cnblogs_post_body\"><p>HTTPWeb APISOARESTfulWeb APIWeb APIHTTPHTTPWebWeb<a href=\"https://liuyanzhao.com/tag/java/\" title=\" Java \" target=\"_blank\">Java</a>scriptAJAXJSONHTML5PHPJSPASP.NETWeb API + RIAWeb APIRIAWeb API<a href=\"https://liuyanzhao.com/tag/java/\" title=\" Java \" target=\"_blank\">Java</a><a href=\"https://liuyanzhao.com/tag/java/\" title=\" Java \" target=\"_blank\">Java</a>HTTPWeb APIWeb APIHTTP</p><h2></h2><p>HTTP(Idempotence)HTTP/1.1</p><blockquote><p>Methods can also have the property of \"idempotence\" in that (aside from error or expiration issues) the side-effects of N &gt; 0 identical requests is the same as for a single request.</p></blockquote><p>HTTPHTTPHTTPHTTP</p><h2> vs </h2><p>APIHTTP</p><pre><code>bool withdraw(account_id, amount)\r\n</code></pre><p>withdrawaccount_idamounttrueamountfalsewithdrawwithdraw1</p><p><img src=\"/uploads/2017/10/20171007153621950.png\" alt=\"20171007153621950.png\"><br></p><p>1</p><p>withdrawACID</p><p>withdraw</p><pre><code>int create_ticket() \r\nbool idempotent_withdraw(ticket_id, account_id, amount)\r\n</code></pre><p>create_ticketticket_ididempotent_withdrawwithdrawticket_idticket_ididempotent_withdraw</p><p>1.create_ticket()ticket_id2.idempotent_withdraw(ticket_id, account_id, amount)create_ticketidempotent_withdraw2</p><p><img src=\"/uploads/2017/10/20171007153648208.png\" alt=\"20171007153648208.png\"><br></p><div id=\"cnblogs_post_body\"><p>2</p><p></p><h2>HTTP</h2><p>HTTPHTTPRESTfulHTTPHTTPSOAHTTPHTTPHTTPHTTPRESTfulSOARESTfulWeb APIHTTP GETDELETEPUTPOST</p><p>HTTP GETGET http://www.bank.com/account/123456NNGETGET http://www.news.com/latest-newsHTTP</p><p>HTTP DELETEDELETE http://www.forum.com/article/4231Nid4231</p><p>HTTP POSTPUTPOSTPUTPOSTPUTHTTPPOSTPUT</p><blockquote><p>The POST method is used to request that the origin server accept the entity enclosed in the request as a new subordinate of the resource identified by the Request-URI in the Request-Line ...... If a resource has been created on the origin server, the response SHOULD be 201 (Created) and contain an entity which describes the status of the request and refers to the new resource, and a Location header.</p><p>The PUT method requests that the enclosed entity be stored under the supplied Request-URI. If the Request-URI refers to an already existing resource, the enclosed entity SHOULD be considered as a modified version of the one residing on the origin server. If the Request-URI does not point to an existing resource, and that URI is capable of being defined as a new resource by the requesting user agent, the origin server can create the resource with that URI.</p></blockquote><p>POSTURIPOST http://www.forum.com/articleshttp://www.forum.com/articlesHTTPURIPOSTURIPOSTPUTURIPUT http://www.forum/articles/4231ID4231URIPUTPUTPUT</p><p>Web APIPOST /ticketscreate_ticketPUT /accounts/account_id/ticket_id&amp;amount=xxxidempotent_withdrawamountURIURI/accounts/account_id/ticket_idamountbody</p><h2></h2><p>HTTPN1Wikipedia</p><h2></h2><p><a href=\"https://liuyanzhao.com/wp-content/themes/begin/inc/go.php?url=http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec9.html\">RFC 2616, Hypertext Transfer Protocol -- HTTP/1.1, Method Definitions</a></p><p><a href=\"https://liuyanzhao.com/wp-content/themes/begin/inc/go.php?url=http://devhawk.net/2007/11/09/the-importance-of-idempotence/\">The Importance of Idempotence</a></p><p><a href=\"https://liuyanzhao.com/wp-content/themes/begin/inc/go.php?url=http://stackoverflow.com/questions/630453/put-vs-post-in-rest\">Stackoverflow - PUT vs POST in REST</a></p></div><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://liuyanzhao.com/wp-content/themes/begin/inc/go.php?url=http://www.cnblogs.com/weidagang2046/archive/2011/06/04/idempotence.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">http://www.cnblogs.co